{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d286-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"107"},"text":"§ 107.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Availability of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d287-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Under such regulations as the Secretary concerned may prescribe, appropriations for the National Guard are available for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d288-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the necessary expenses of members of a regular or reserve component of the Army or the Air Force traveling on duty in connection with the National Guard;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d289-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the necessary expenses of members of the Regular Army or the Regular Air Force on duty in the National Guard Bureau or with the Army Staff or the Air Staff, traveling to and from annual conventions of the Enlisted Association of the National Guard of the United States, the National Guard Association of the United States, or the Adjutants General Association;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28a-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the transportation of supplies furnished to the National Guard as permanent equipment;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28b-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the office rent and necessary office expenses of officers of a regular or reserve component of the Army or the Air Force on duty with the National Guard;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28c-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the expenses of the National Guard Bureau, including clerical services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28d-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the promotion of rifle practice, including the acquisition, construction, maintenance, and equipment of shooting galleries and suitable target ranges;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28e-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such incidental expenses of authorized encampments, maneuvers, and field instruction as the Secretary considers necessary; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d28f-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other expenses of the National Guard authorized by law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d290-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The expenses of enlisted members of the Regular Army or the Regular Air Force on duty with the National Guard shall be paid from appropriations for the Army National Guard or the Air National Guard, as the case may be, but not from the allotment of a State, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the District of Columbia, Guam, or the Virgin Islands. Payable expenses include allowances for subsistence and housing under sections 402 and 403 of title 37 and expenses for medicine and medical attendance.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d291-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95","identifier":"/us/usc/t32/s107/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The pay and allowances for the Chief of the National Guard Bureau and officers of the Army National Guard of the United States or the Air National Guard of the United States called to active duty under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12402"},"text":"section 12402 of title 10","children":[],"tail":" shall be paid from appropriations for the pay of the Army National Guard or Air National Guard."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida1c3d292-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/599"},"text":"70A Stat. 599","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/83/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–83, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-09-11"},"text":"Sept. 11, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/220"},"text":"81 Stat. 220","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/119/s1/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–119, § 1(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1971","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/85/340"},"text":"85 Stat. 340","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s2/h"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 2(h)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1061"},"text":"96 Stat. 1061","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456/dA/tXII/s1234/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456, div. A, title XII, § 1234(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2059"},"text":"102 Stat. 2059","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1676/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1676(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3019"},"text":"108 Stat. 3019","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/dA/tVI/s603/d/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, div. A, title VI, § 603(d)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1783"},"text":"111 Stat. 1783","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tV/s514/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, div. A, title V, § 514(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-24"},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1460"},"text":"117 Stat. 1460","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/dA/tX/s1057/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, div. A, title X, § 1057(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3441"},"text":"119 Stat. 3441","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida1c3d293-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida1c3d294-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"ida1c3d295-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"1956 ","children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"107(a)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"107(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"107(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"32:22 (less proviso).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"32:22 (proviso, less words between 5th and 7th semicolons).","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"32:22 (words between 5th and 7th semicolons of proviso).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1916-06-03/ch134/s67"},"text":"June 3, 1916, ch. 134, § 67","children":[],"tail":" (2d par.), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/199"},"text":"39 Stat. 199","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-22/ch423/s3"},"text":"Sept. 22, 1922, ch. 423, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/1034"},"text":"42 Stat. 1034","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-04-06/ch321"},"text":"Apr. 6, 1928, ch. 321","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/406"},"text":"45 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “strengths in enlisted members of the active” are substituted for the words “number of enlisted men in active service”. The words between the eighth and ninth semicolons of 32:22, relating to horses and draft animals, are omitted as obsolete, since no animals are now authorized for the National Guard. The words “under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t32/s106"},"text":"section 106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are inserted, since only appropriations under that revised section are required to be apportioned."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(1) and (2), the words “actual and” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(2), the words “Reserve Officers holding commission in the National Guard” are omitted as covered by the words “officers of a * * * reserve component of the Army or the Air Force”. The words “Army General Staff” are substituted for the words “War Department General Staff” to conform to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3031/b"},"text":"section 3031(b) of title 10","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “under sections 251 and 252 of title 37” are substituted for the words “provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s19"},"text":"section 19 of title 37","children":[],"tail":"”, since allowances for subsistence and quarters are now covered by those sections. The words “shall be paid from appropriations for the National Guard, but not from the allotment of a State or Territory, Puerto Rico, the Canal Zone, or the District of Columbia” are substituted for the words “shall constitute a charge against the whole sum annually appropriated for the support of the National Guard, and shall be paid therefrom and not from the allotment duly apportioned for any particular State, Territory, or the District of Columbia”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"ida1c3d296-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"ida1c3d297-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"1982","children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":" Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"32:107(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"31:698.","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041/s30"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041, § 30","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/632"},"text":"70A Stat. 632","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The work “appropriations” is substituted for “funds appropriated” for consistency in the title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida1c3d298-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida1c3d299-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" substituted “State, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the District of Columbia, Guam, or the Virgin Islands” for “State or Territory, Puerto Rico, or the District of Columbia”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136","children":[],"tail":" substituted “members” for “officers”, “Army Staff” for “Army General Staff”, and “the Enlisted Association of the National Guard of the United States, the National Guard Association of the United States,” for “the National Guard Association of the United States”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85","children":[],"tail":" substituted “and housing” for “and quarters”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" substituted “12402” for “3496 or 8496”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456","children":[],"tail":" struck out “the Canal Zone,” after “Puerto Rico,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1971—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/119/s1/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–119, § 1(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Availability” for “Apportionment” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/119/s1/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–119, § 1(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), (4), redesignated subsec. (b) as (a) and substituted “appropriation for the National Guard” for “apportioned appropriation”. Former subsec. (a), which provided for apportionment of appropriations for Army National Guard and Air National Guard under prescribed formulas among States, territories, Puerto Rico, Canal Zone, District of Columbia, was struck out."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (b), (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/119/s1/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–119, § 1(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (c) as (b). Former subsec. (b) redesignated (a) and amended."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–83","children":[],"tail":" substituted “402 and 403” for “251 and 252”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida1c3d29a-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida1c3d29b-2930-11f1-9ed5-c078b45cfa95"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2003 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tV/s514/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136, div. A, title V, § 514(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-11-24"},"text":"Nov. 24, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/1460"},"text":"117 Stat. 1460","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/136/dA/tV/s514/b"},"text":"“The amendments made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall not apply with respect to funds appropriated for a fiscal year before f